[SHORT DESC]
Summons rain for five turns.

[LONG DESC]
<p>Summons rain for five turns. If the user is holding the item Damp Rock, it lasts for eight turns instead. While in effect, it increases the damage of Water-type moves by 50%, and causes Fire-type moves to do half damage. Thunder always hits (and has a chance to hit through Detect and Protect equal to 100% minus the accuracy against a non-Protected opponent). SolarBeam has 60 Base Power. Moonlight, Morning Sun, and Synthesis heal 1/4 of the user's maximum HP. Pokémon with the Swift Swim ability have double Speed. Pokémon with the Forecast ability become Water-type. At the end of each turn, Pokémon with the Rain Dish ability heal 1/16 HP, Pokémon with the Dry Skin ability heal 1/8 HP, and Pokémon with the Hydration ability cure themselves of status ailments.</p>

<p><a href="/dp/articles/rain_offense">Smogon has an article on this topic.</a>

<h2>Related Moves</h2>
<p><a href="/dp/moves/hail">Hail</a> is an Ice-type equivalent.<br/ >
<a href="/dp/moves/sandstorm">Sandstorm</a> is a Rock-type equivalent.<br/ >
<a href="/dp/moves/sunny_day">Sunny Day</a> is a Fire-type equivalent.</p>